m at the University of Arizona, and now in retirement continues actively to write and publish. In this volume, 46 of his colleagues and students contribute essays in his honor, reflecting the broad scope of his interests, particularly in terms of the historical implications of archaeology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh1 aAbadi, Yael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAckerman, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAckermann, Oren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbertz, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBen-Tor, Amnon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBietak, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruins, Hendrik J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuccellati, Giorgio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBunimovitz, Shlomo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDessel, J. P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDothan, Trude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreedman, David Noel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFritz, Volkmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGitin, Seymour (Sy), eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGittlen, Barry M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGottwald, Norman K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreenberg, Raphael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalpern, Baruch, econtributor.4ct